Vice President Mike Pence spoke at the 2019 AIPAC Policy Conference in Washington, D.C., where he addressed the progress made in the alliance between the United States and Israel. He highlighted President Trump's actions, such as moving the American embassy to Jerusalem and recognizing Israel's sovereignty over the Golan Heights. Pence also condemned anti-Semitism and criticized Democrats who have made anti-Israel remarks. He reaffirmed the United States' commitment to standing with Israel and opposing Iran's influence in the region. Pence concluded by expressing his belief in a bright future for both Israel and the United States.